        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">The date is established by CD’s annotation.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f2">CD was gathering data for his research on the action of worms. In <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_2241.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Earthworms</hi></ref>, pp. 292–7, CD discussed the gradual disappearance of ridges and furrows on inclined land.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f3">CD described the location of the two sections or square yards and the weight of the castings produced in each section in <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_2241.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Earthworms</hi></ref>, pp. 165–8. In this account, he referred to Wedgwood as ‘a lady’.</note>
